  "text": "let's discuss visual influences on works.\n---\n\nI've wasted a lot of weeks this year on procrastination, watching stupid normie shit, as I've just realized. The constant entertainment with liveleak videos, memes, worthless tv series eventually gets you nowhere. You might tell yourself \"oh, maybe I can find inspiration in that!\", but it's hardly ever the case. Out of a hundred shitty videos that I've watched, one half-stupid idea for a work has emerged. At best. \n\nThis is why I say to you, you are what you eat. Look at /ic/. It is flooded with porn art. You draw porn, because you watch way too much porn. It has polluted your mind completely. And actually porn as \"reference for nudes\" is useless and deceptive, as you work from a shitty compressed screenshot of a film from most likely an extremely distorted wide-angle lense video. Which is why a lot of porn art has the very same distortions as porn. \n\nWhether it's porn, some netflix shit show, funny videos, memes, anime. You are most likely feeding your visual library with a lot of junk. The worst kind is really the normie shit, because it's letting your mind stagnate in low-tier entertainment. Where is the crazy stuff in that?\nTurn off the internet. Feed yourself obscure art, niche music, good films, art exhibitions …\n\nYou see a lot of \"I tried and failed\" threads on here and people who complain about having not enough motivation. Go on a diet, get the shit out of your system, turn the fucking internet off and draw for a week straight. \n\nPost results in here, if the thread is still alive. General discussion.",
