  "text": "just a heads up about your use of hiragana to write the word, \"black\"\n\nBorrowed words, or words and names from other languages use a different alphabet called katakana. It looks a bit cooler, too. The enlish word for black, then (a japanese speaker would say buraku if they were imitating the english) would be written ブラック。\n\nHowever, if you wanted to say black in japanese it would be kuroi, which is written 黒い in kanji, orくろい in hiragana.\n\nsmall language lesson",
