  "text": "I'd recommend an HP Envy or Spectre x360. Been running one for 6 months and it's pretty damn nice. Most models also support AES and N Trig stylus', so you got a bit of wiggle room there.\nThere are some refurbished models on eBay running between $500 - $600. The ones good for your price range would probably be the ones running either a Ryzen 5 2500u, or an Intel i5 8250u. Both have fairly similar CPU power, the 8250u probably edges out the Ryzen by a few percent, but the 2500u has much greater graphics power (relatively speaking, these still are integrated graphics of course).\nI'd recommend replacing the HDD with an SSD whenever you can though, I've been needing to do that for a while now.",
