  "text": "Honestly, just by practicing helps the most, literally getting better and knowing you're better.\n\nAlso understanding and valuing your work and learning to see that it's important. And that's not delusional, human beings are made to make things, we've got two dexterous hands and a brain capable of imagination and invention. making things is among the most virtuous acts you can do as a human being. Even making bad work can have a dignity that's far better than making no work at all. Think of it that way. When you start to worry about the merits and condition of your own work and recognize it as completely unique and separate from any others, a product of your completely unique experience and touch, then you start not to hate or consider other artists. You just make your art, and that's got nothing to do with anyone else.",
